race.comment: OTAGO (2) resumes and is the class runner in this race, hence the weight. He's had his issues with injury but was very good in two runs last time in, only beaten by the talented, Group class horse King Zephyr first up before trying hard as favourite in a BM84. He'll need a touch of luck from the inside gate but should be very hard to hold out if he's near his best. DEEP PLEASURE (5) is a progressive mare herself, okay last time in stronger company at Caulfield having been very good in two runs prior. Shinn goes on and she should run very well. ASTRAL FLAME (9) was turned over as favourite fresh but will come on from that and has ability. ACID WASH (3) could be an improver, his best is good enough.
